<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-4145] Statically imported fields &amp; properties</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-4145</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Create class Foo&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;Foo {
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;static&lt;/span&gt; foo=2
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;static&lt;/span&gt; getFoo(){
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; 3
  } 
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;and a script &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;static&lt;/span&gt; Foo.foo

print foo
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This script calls getter getFoo and prints &quot;3&quot;.&lt;br/&gt;
But if you delete declaration &quot;static foo=2&quot; from the class the script fails with MissingPropertyException. &lt;br/&gt;
IMHO the script should call getter in both cases.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
